alse, "description": "Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2019-03-07T01:47:07Z", "updated_at": "2019-03-09T02:22:34Z", "closed_at": "2019-03-09T02:22:34Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This example prints `test 1 2 3` when compiled and run in debug mode:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(c_variadic)]\r\n\r\nextern \"C\" {\r\n    #[no_mangle]\r\n    fn vprintf(_: *const libc::c_char, _: ...) -> libc::c_int;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#[no_mangle]\r\nunsafe extern \"C\" fn variadic(fmt: *const libc::c_char, a: ...)\r\n -> libc::c_int {\r\n    vprintf(fmt, a)\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let fmt = std::ffi::CString::new(\"test %d %d %d\\n\").expect(\"new failed\");\r\n    unsafe {\r\n        variadic(fmt.as_ptr(), 1, 2, 3);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCompiling and running in release mode causes a segfault in [`glibc/stdio-common/vfprintf.c:1286`](https://code.woboq.org/userspace/glibc/stdio-common/vfprintf.c.html#1296) because `ap`  is nul. Enabling debug info in release mode via `Cargo.toml` makes the segfault go away.\r\n\r\n## Meta\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ rustc --version --verbose\r\nrustc 1.35.0-nightly (f22dca0a1 2019-03-05)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: f22dca0a1bef4141e75326caacc3cd59f3d5be8e\r\ncommit-date: 2019-03-05\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.35.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 8.0\r\n```", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_